to Bill Niman to Wolfgang Puck—Inside the California Food Revolution demonstrates that, while fresh produce and locally sourced ingredients are iconic in California, what transforms these elements into a unique cuisine is a distinctly Western culture of openness, creativity, and collaboration. Engagingly written and full of captivating anecdotes, this book shows how the inspirations that emerged in California went on to transform the experience of eating throughout the United States and the world.    aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCookingxCalifornia style. 0aCookingzCaliforniaxHistory. 0aCooking, AmericanxCalifornia stylexHistory. 0aRestaurantsxHistoryxCalifornia. 0aRestaurantszCaliforniaxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh  aamerican cuisine.  abold innovation.  abooks on food.  acalifornia cooking.  acalifornia cuisine.  acalifornia studies in food.  acaptivating anecdotes.  aconventional kitchen.  acooking.  aculinary.  aengaging.  aethnic food.  afamous chefs.  afarm to table.  afine dining.  afood and drink.  afood and wine.  afood studies.  afood writing.  afood.  afoodie books.  aforaging.  afusion cooking.  agastronomy.  ahistory.  ainformal food scene.  ainsiders account.  ainterviews.  alively.  aregional cooking.  asourced ingredients.  awestern culture.  awolfgang puck.  awonderful interviews.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095670440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520956704423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520956704/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Pr